Scene 1: Overview: The user in this experience is portrayed as a Formula-1 driver in the beginning as they will be wearing the racing suit and will have various things that a F1 driver needs. In the opening scene, the user is in a personal cool-down room provided to the F1 driver to relax. This is like a starting zone for the user to settle into the VR experience. It is a standard room with a table, couch, and wardrobe. It consists of different interactable objects like water bottles and soda can on a table and other things like helmet, racing suit and racing shoes. <img src=" racing suit is hanging, at the corner of that wall on right there is the helmet of the user which is kept on a small table. The user can also see the (text-colour:yellow)["i" symbol pop-up] on items such as helmet and racing suit. So, if the user approaches and select that pop-up, it will give more information of that item in the form of small text window near that item and voice narration. (text-colour:red)[On the right side of the user], there is a door and next to that is a desk, the user can see the glowing items on the table such as the (text-colour:grey)[water bottles and can of energy drink]. The user can interact with any of these glowing obejects. For eg, the user can hold the can of energy, after which the user is instructed with hand gesture to open the can. Here, a power bar is visible to user and by applying optimal power in green zone, the user can open the can. On the left wall, at the front corner there is a small wardrobe and the user can see multiple pair of racing shoes kept under the wardrobe, there is an "i" symbol pop up on the shoes as well. On the immediate left side of user, there is a couch. There is also sound of engine revving from the Formula-1 cars that passes the track at high-speed coming from the back of the user. So, if the user walks near the back window and the sound of cars passing increases. Through the window the user can also view a small part of the racing track.. So, In this starting zone the user can learn the basics control that he/she will require in the future experience. After a short time frame, there will a knock on the door and naturally the user would react to the sound and look at the door. There will be a pop-up on the door handle, which instructs the user to open the door with a “hand gesture” sign. "> [[Scene 3: Route to the garage]]Scene 3: Once the user selects a F1 team, the manager congratulates the user and instructs the user to follow him to the garage of the selected team. The user will be instructed to follow the manager using a pop-up of a joystick figure to move forward. The user will be then escorted to the pit lane, which is on the side of the track, where there are garages of all the teams in line through a short-fixed route. As the user walks towards to the garage and race track, the sound of F1 car engine and wheel guns increases. Then there will be a transition from the indoor building to outside part of race track, where there will be sunlight, clear sky. The user can see the pit lane entry [[Scene 4: Garage and Paddock ]]The manager and the player reaches the garage of the selected team, where the user can also have a glimpse of the garages of other teams. The manager then introduces the user to the team principal and leaves the player to explore the garage. The team principal greets the user, hands him/her a pair of headphones, and instructs him/her to wear them. If the user does not take any action, a hand gesture pop-up will appear beside the headphones with instructions on how to wear them by taking them with two hands and bringing them close to the user’s ear. The headphones act as a mode of communication whenever there is some instruction or guidance which needs to be provided to the user, and it is done through voice narration and small text window pop-up. The user is then asked to select a racing number which would appear on the F1 car and is informed to have a look at his/her new racing suit and helmet in the garage. [[Pop-ups in the garage]] [[Pit Stop]] The player can move around the garage and explore the F1 car, which is kept in the center of the room. There are numerous “i” symbol pop-ups on various areas of the car such as the front wing, side pods, rear wing and engine that provide information about it. The user can select any pop up which would give him/her information of it in voice narration and text window. The user can also see glowing objects, such as the car's steering wheel on the table on the left side and other interactable objects include the TV remote, which allows the user to turn the television on and off as well as view the information offered by the team on the TV. A "red alert" pop-up can also be seen at the driver seat in car, when the user selects that he/she gets an instruction to take the steering wheel and sit in the car. So, the user is guided with an arrow on the steering wheel and he/she is then instructed to stand close to car, after which the player can automatically sit in the car. Inside the car, the user can have a view of a Formula-1 driver with the steering wheel in front. The user is then instructed to start the car by pushing some buttons on the steering wheel for a test. The team principal explains the user all controls on steering wheel through voice naration. After the test start up, the user is instructed to leave the car by hand gestures. There is also a tire rack on the side with an “i” pop-up where the user can acquire information on all of the different types of tires and when to choose which one. Other than that, the player can also interact with other available object, such as the wheel, and can bounce them on the floor or throw them, and it would behave like a normal F1 tire in a real-world scenario. [[Scene 4: Garage and Paddock ]]Once the user gets all the basic information about the tires, a message pops up through the headphones with voice of team principal and a small text pop up window, that the team is short of a mechanic for pit stop and he/she will have to perform a pit stop. After that, the user is instructed through voice message as well as a pop up near the tire rack, to grab a specific set of tire based on decided strategy as fast as possible. There can be 4 sets of tires: 1) Soft tires (red strip on side) 2) Medium tires (yellow strip on side) 3) Hard tires (white strip on side) 4) Wet tires (green strip on side) Once, the user gets the correct set of tire, he/she is then instructed to go outside the garage by guiding arrows on ground and sit at specified spot near the pit area outside garage with the tire. The user is then given a choice to get a tutorial on pit stop or skip it. In the tutorial, the player is taught with the basics of using a wheel gun. First, he/she is instructed to pick a the wheel gun with a hand gesture on it. After that, the user can see a power bar near the wheel gun and then he/she is instructed to operate the gun by pressing a button, the more button the user presses the more power the gun will generate. So, the user is instructed to keep the power in the green range when using it for pit stop. A demo pit stop is then performed where the user is instructed with a step by step process when to use the wheel gun, after using the wheel gun remove the old tire and keep it aside, take the new tire and place in proper position on wheel rim, and then use to wheel gun to fit the new wheel. After the user completes the tutorial he/she can experience a real timed pit stop, where the car comes in the pit lane box and the user is supposed to remove the old set of tires and install new ones on it. The user can save the time of each pit-stop and compete with all the player around the world. In order to improve and perform the pit stop again, the user can find the option for it near the tire rack. In this scene, as the user opens the door the manager of the user enters the room. He then introduces himself and congratulates the user for making it to Formula-1 and explains how he will help the user to select a contract offered to him/her from different Formula-1 teams. After that, the manager hands the user a tablet which contains information of multiple F1 teams with their performance rating and view of their car, the player is instructed with a swipe gesture pop-up near the tablet in order to view next team. The manager instructs the user to select any one of the team based on the performance level while the player is viewing all the option on the tablet <img "> Once the user finalizes a Formula - 1 team, the manager congratulates and instructs the user to follow him to the garage of the selected team.
